This article is a presidential memorandum from Barack Obama, the President of the United States, dated January 15, 2013. The memorandum delegates certain functions to the Secretary of State under Section 6 of Public Law 112-150. The President delegates these functions by the authority vested in him by the Constitution and the laws of the United States. The Secretary of State is instructed to exercise these functions in coordination with the Secretary of Defense. The memorandum also authorizes and directs the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.